Goodyear Lastikleri TAS (GOODY) , the Turkish
unit of  Goodyear Tire & Rubber Co. (GT) , fell to the lowest in more
than two weeks after first-quarter profit plummeted 50 percent.  Goodyear Lastikleri dropped 4.5 percent to 53.50 liras at
the close in Istanbul, the weakest since April 17, extending the
companyâ€™s retreat this week to 10 percent.  First-quarter net income declined to 12.6 million liras
($7.2 million) from 25.2 million liras a year ago, according to
a filing with the Istanbul Stock Exchange after the market
closed yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
